# React Component Patterns

## File Organization

- **Pages** → `client/src/pages/` — one file per route, PascalCase (e.g., `ProductDetail.tsx`)
- **Reusable components** → `client/src/components/` — shared across pages
- **UI primitives** → `client/src/components/ui/` — shadcn/ui components, don't modify directly
- **Hooks** → `client/src/hooks/` — custom hooks extracted from components
- **Contexts** → `client/src/contexts/` — React contexts for cross-cutting concerns

## Component Guidelines

- Functional components only — no class components
- Export named functions, not default exports: `export function ProductCard() {}`
- Co-locate component-specific logic; extract to hooks when reused
- Props interface defined above the component, not inline

## Data Fetching

```tsx
// Read data
const { data, isLoading, error } = trpc.products.myProducts.useQuery();

// Write data
const mutation = trpc.products.addToMyThings.useMutation({
  onSuccess: () => {
    utils.products.myProducts.invalidate();
    toast.success("Product added");
  },
  onError: (err) => toast.error(err.message),
});
```

- Never use raw `fetch()` — all API calls go through tRPC hooks
- Show loading skeletons (see `ProductCardSkeleton`) during `isLoading`
- Show `EmptyState` component when data array is empty

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Use `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional classes
- Follow design system tokens from `index.css` (colors, spacing, typography)
- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, `md:` for larger screens
- Bottom padding: add `pb-24` on scrollable pages to clear bottom nav (80px)

## Routing (Wouter)

- Register all routes in `App.tsx` using `<Route path="/..." component={...} />`
- Navigate with `useLocation()` hook: `const [, setLocation] = useLocation()`
- Link with `<Link href="/path">` — not `<a>` tags for internal navigation

## Accessibility

- Touch targets ≥44px × 44px
- All images have `alt` text
- Interactive elements use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<a>`, `<input>`)
- Color contrast meets WCAG AA (check against design doc tokens)
